title: Math TASC Practice Test 1
intro_text:
Mathematics

Welcome to the TASC Mathematics Initial Practice Test!

There are 21 questions. The goal is to give you practice on the types of questions you will see on the actual TASC Test and to give you a study plan for what you need to brush up on for the test.

You may use a calculator for Questions 1-15. No calculator is allowed for Questions 16-21.

We'll use your results to help create your learning plan and make recommendations as you move through the course.

Take your time with this test. If you don't know how to answer a question, leave it blank and go on to the next question. Guessing is a good idea on the actual test, but for this test, we really want to understand what you know. If you are unsure of an answer and want to think about it, you can click “Review Question Later” to come back to the question later.

Relax and do your best!
